                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-defend1816" type="age" value="20"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18280911-333-off1714" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-off1714" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-off1714" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280911-333-cd1715" type="crimeDate">5th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-333-off1714 t18280911-333-cd1715"></join>, 75lbs. of lead, value 10s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18280911-333-victim1817" type="victimName">
                        Thomas 
                        Miller
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-victim1817" type="surname" value="Miller"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280911-333-victim1817" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280911-333-victim1817" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-333-off1714 t18280911-333-victim1817"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , and fixed to a certain building
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>THOMAS MILLER. The house in question is mine. I have lost two or three cwt. of lead at different times.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-333-person1818">
                  GEORGE 
                  TWEEDY
               <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1818" type="surname" value="TWEEDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1818" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1818" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Miller. On the 4th of July I saw this lead safe; the prisoner was stopped next morning - I was sent for, and compared the lead, it fitted exactly, nail holes and all.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-333-person1819">
                  RICHARD 
                  BURT
               <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1819" type="surname" value="BURT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1819" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1819" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going to market that morning and saw a man come out of the court with a load; I went to Woodgate's door and told him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-333-person1820">
                  GEORGE 
                  WOODGATE
               <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1820" type="surname" value="WOODGATE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1820" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1820" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Burt gave me information; I went, and overtook the prisoner near Pitfield-street, with a soot bag, which he was resting on a post - I took hold of it, and it contained lead; I compared it with the roof of Mr. Miller's house, it fitted exactly.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-333-person1821">
                  JOHN 
                  SHAW
               <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1821" type="surname" value="SHAW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1821" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1821" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I was called to assist a man over the road; I went over to the George the Fourth public-house, and took the prisoner - I saw the lead fitted - it appeared quite right.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-333-person1822">
                  DANIEL 
                  NEWTON
               <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1822" type="surname" value="NEWTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1822" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1822" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was on the parapet on the 4th - the lead was all safe; next morning I saw this fitted.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-333-person1823">
                  MARY 
                  STEWARD
               <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1823" type="surname" value="STEWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1823" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-person1823" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am bar-maid at the George the Fourth: the lead was left there - we let them have the same again.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going down the court, saw the lead lying down, and put into my bag.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-333-verdict1716" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-333-verdict1716" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20.</p>
